This installation is set up to be managed by pipenv.

(0) If you do not have pipenv, install it.
On a Mac with homebrew, "brew install pipenv" should work.
To install pypy3 with homebrew, run "brew install pypy3"

(1) On a newly-spawned cloud Ubuntu box you want these steps

cd                                          # be in the right place
[[ -d blockstuff ]] && rm -rf blockstuff    # and that it's clean
git clone https://github.com/jsh/blockstuff # get the repo
cd blockstuff
git checkout hybrid-oo                      # the right branch
./linux.sh                                  # everything else
